接口 Observer<T>

  • 类型参数:
    T - the type of item the Observer expects to observe
    所有已知子接口:
    AsyncEmitter<T>
    所有已知实现类:
    ActionNotificationObserver, ActionObserver, ActionSubscriber, AsyncSubject, BehaviorSubject, BlockingOperatorToIterator.SubscriberIterator, BufferUntilSubscriber, DeferredScalarSubscriber, DeferredScalarSubscriberSafe, ObserverSubscriber, OnSubscribePublishMulticast, OperatorGroupBy.GroupBySubscriber, ProducerObserverArbiter, PublishSubject, QueuedProducer, ReplaySubject, SafeSubscriber, SerializedObserver, SerializedSubject, SerializedSubscriber, Subject, Subscriber, TestObserver, TestSubject, TestSubscriber, UnicastSubject

    public interface Observer<T>
    Provides a mechanism for receiving push-based notifications.

    After an Observer calls an Observable's subscribe method, the Observable calls the Observer's onNext(T) method to provide notifications. A well-behaved Observable will call an Observer's onCompleted() method exactly once or the Observer's onError(java.lang.Throwable) method exactly once.

    另请参阅:
    ReactiveX documentation: Observable

    • 方法概要

      所有方法 实例方法 抽象方法 
      限定符和类型 方法和说明
      void onCompleted()
      Notifies the Observer that the Observable has finished sending push-based notifications.
      void onError(java.lang.Throwable e)
      Notifies the Observer that the Observable has experienced an error condition.
      void onNext(T t)
      Provides the Observer with a new item to observe.

    • 方法详细资料

      • onCompleted

        void onCompleted()
        Notifies the Observer that the Observable has finished sending push-based notifications.

        The Observable will not call this method if it calls onError(java.lang.Throwable).

      • onError

        void onError(java.lang.Throwable e)
        Notifies the Observer that the Observable has experienced an error condition.

        If the Observable calls this method, it will not thereafter call onNext(T) or onCompleted().

        参数:
        e - the exception encountered by the Observable

      • onNext

        void onNext(T t)
        Provides the Observer with a new item to observe.

        The Observable may call this method 0 or more times.

        The Observable will not call this method again after it calls either onCompleted() or onError(java.lang.Throwable).

        参数:
        t - the item emitted by the Observable
